sentence: Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 20, 2016.
A cash dividend payment of $0.6695 per share is scheduled to be paid on August 15, 2016.
Shareholders who purchased PG prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment.
This represents an 1% increase over prior dividend payment.
At the current stock price of $85.93, the dividend yield is 3.12%.
The previous trading day's last sale of PG was $85.93, representing a -1.1% decrease from the 52 week high of $86.89 and a 32.16% increase over the 52 week low of $65.02.
PG is a part of the Basic Industries sector, which includes companies such as Unilever PLC ( UL ) and Unilever NV ( UN ).
PG's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $3.18.
Zacks Investment Research reports PG's forecasted earnings growth in 2016 as -9.93%, compared to an industry average of 4.3%.
For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the PG Dividend History page.
